---
import { getCollection, getEntries } from "astro:content";
import "../styles/base.css";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import MilestoneCard from "../components/MilestoneCard.astro";
import Card from "../components/Card.astro";

let allMilestones = await getCollection("milestones");

// set the type to be milestone + items
allMilestones = await Promise.all(
  allMilestones.map(async (milestone) => ({
    ...milestone,
    items: await getEntries(milestone.data.items),
  })),
);
---

<Layout title="Swarm Roadmap">
  <main class="pt-12 pb-24 md:pb-48 text-[19px] leading-[26px] text-[#F6F7F9]">
    <div class="flex justify-center">
      <a href="https://www.ethswarm.org/"
        ><img src="/swarm.png" alt="" class="h-9" /></a
      >
    </div>

    <div
      class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 lg:px-8 pb-16 lg:pb-24 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-5 border border-transparent pt-8 lg:pt-0"
    >
      <div class="flex flex-col justify-center">
        <h1
          class="text-6xl md:text-[88px] font-bold leading-[97px] tracking-tight"
        >
          Roadmap
        </h1>

        <div class="mt-6 md:mr-20 max-w-md">
          <p>
            <strong
              >Embarking on the Journey to Swarm 3.0: A Year of Groundbreaking
              Developments</strong
            >
          </p>
          <br />
          <p>
            As we venture through 2024, each release under the Swarm initiative
            brings us closer to the realization of Swarm 3.0, an epoch where
            decentralized data storage transforms into a ubiquitous utility,
            seamlessly integrated into our daily lives.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 md:mt-0 lg:py-14 lg:pl-20 mx-auto">
        <img
          class="h-[368px] lg:h-[603px] w-auto object-contain"
          src="/background.png"
          alt=""
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <div
      class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 lg:px-8 pt-16 md:pt-24 pb-20 md:pb-36 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-10 border border-transparent"
    >
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <p>
          This journey is not just a series of software updates; itâ€™s a
          revolution in how we access and manage data. <strong
            >Swarm 3.0 envisions a world where data privacy, security, and
            accessibility are inherent rights.</strong
          > With every milestone, we lay the groundwork for a future where decentralised
          storage and services empower individuals and businesses, fostering innovation
          and creating new economic opportunities.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <p>
          The transition to Swarm 3.0 is about building a resilient and scalable
          infrastructure that supports the digital demands of tomorrow, ensuring
          data is stored, accessed, and utilised in a fair and equitable manner. <strong
            >This roadmap outlines the steps we are taking this year to make
            this vision a reality, highlighting the technological advancements
            and strategic initiatives that will drive us forward.</strong
          >
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div
      class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-5 lg:px-10 flex flex-col gap-12 lg:gap-20 xl:gap-24"
    >
      {
        allMilestones.map((milestone) => (
          // @ts-ignore
          <MilestoneCard
            title={milestone.data.title}
            items={milestone.items}
            slug={milestone.slug}
            percentage={milestone.data.percentage}
            index={milestone.data.index}
          />
        ))
      }
    </div>

    <div
      class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 lg:px-8 pt-16 md:pt-24 pb-24 md:pb-36 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-10 border border-transparent"
    >
      <div>
        <p>
          <strong
            >Each step at the roadmap we take is a bold stride towards
            transforming Swarm into the world's computer, where decentralized
            storage is not just a tool, but a transformational force for
            business, innovation, and everyday life.</strong
          > Emphasizing a fair data economy, we are committed to ensuring that data
          ownership and profit are equitably distributed among all participants.
          Join us on this journey to redefine the digital landscape and establish
          a new paradigm of fairness and accessibility in data management.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p>
          The dates and milestones outlined in this roadmap are subject to
          change.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 lg:px-8 border border-transparent">
      <h2
        class="font-bold text-[48px] leading-[1.2] tracking-tight text-center"
      >
        Vision
      </h2>

      <div
        class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3 gap-5 mt-10 md:mt-16"
      >
        <Card
          title="End Users"
          content="End users have a smooth experience starting a node and have the tools to monitor and interact with their local node. Apps connect to nodes and gateways in a secure way. Basic functionality of websites (files and directories) upload and download is optimised for speed and reliability."
        />
        <Card
          title="Dapp Developers"
          content="Dapp Developers are provided with a mature toolkit that can be used to integrate Swarm in their Web3 dapp. This includes extensive and useful documentation, example dapps, and tutorials. They benefit from dashboards monitoring vital metrics displaying the node's operational health. Developers can rely on help provided in dev channels."
        />
        <Card
          title="Operators"
          content="Node operators are sufficiently incentivised to contribute their bandwidth and storage space. Time-based allowance is calibrated so that clients paying for bandwidth will get reasonable service. As for storage, Postage Stamp revenue is redistributed to storer nodes directly in an efficient way without the need for storage contributors to stake their tokens."
        />
        <Card
          title="Collaborators"
          content="Alternative client development is supported by consolidated and structured specifications of the DISC protocols and client strategies. High level standards and APIs are cleared up and documented. Integration, multiclient testing environment and quality assurance tools are provided. Ecosystem projects are provided with grants and fellowships."
        />
        <Card
          title="Community"
          content="The Swarm Foundation aims to assist as much as it can in providing scaffoldings to the community to support their own agenda involving Swarm. It encourages autonomous, independent and permissionless communities to take further ownership over the protocol and its usages."
        />
        <Card
          title="Commons"
          content="The Foundation subsidises efforts to make large datasets of public interest available through Swarm."
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
